ACAS_N,AMP-binding,AMP-binding_C,DUF779 Catalyzes the conversion of acetate into acetyl-CoA (AcCoA), an essential intermediate at the junction of anabolic and catabolic pathways. AcsA undergoes a two-step reaction. In the first half reaction, AcsA combines acetate with ATP to form acetyl-adenylate (AcAMP) intermediate. In the second half reaction, it can then transfer the acetyl group from AcAMP to the sulfhydryl group of CoA, forming the product AcCoA
Aldedh Belongs to the aldehyde dehydrogenase family
WGR Proposed nucleic acid binding domain
